     # Main orchestrator\n├── config.py           # Configuration\n├── harness/            # Benchmark harnesses\n│   ├── base.py         # Abstract base\n│   ├── swe_bench.py    # SWE-bench implementation\n│   └── humaneval.py    # HumanEval implementation\n├── metrics/            # Collection and analysis\n│   ├── collector.py    # Metrics collection\n│   └── analyzer.py    # Statistical analysis\n└── utils/\n    ├── isolation.py    # Process isolation\n    └── logging.py      # JSON logging\n\ndata/\n├── raw/                # Per-task JSON logs\n└── results/            # Aggregated CSV\n\nscripts/\n├── run_experiment.sh   # Entry point\n└── analyze_results.py  # Post-processing\n```\n\n## Reproducibility\n\n### Docker\n\n```bash\ndocker build -t simplicity-experiment .\ndocker run -v $(pwd)/data:/app/data simplicity-experiment\n```\n\n### Configuration\n\nEdit `experiment/config.py` to modify:\n- Number of tasks per benchmark\n- Timeout settings\n- Agent model\n- Skill configurations\n\n## Citation\n\nIf you use this experiment framework, please cite:\n\n```bibtex\n@article{simplicity2026,\n  title={On the Impact of Laws of Simplicity Skill on the Efficiency of AI Coding Agents},\n  author={...},\n  journal={arXiv preprint},\n  year={2026}\n}\n```\n\n## License\n\nMIT License\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Commit experiment documentation**\n\n```bash\ngit add experiment/README.md\ngit commit -m \"docs: add experiment README\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n### Task 11.1: Smoke Test\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Verify all imports work correctly**\n\n```bash\npython -c \"\nfrom experiment.config import DEFAULT_CONFIG\nfrom experiment.harness.base import BenchmarkHarness, TaskResult, TaskSpec\nfrom experiment.harness.swe_bench import SWEBenchHarness\nfrom experiment.harness.humaneval import HumanEvalHarness\nfrom experiment.metrics.collector import MetricsCollector\nfrom experiment.metrics.analyzer import run_full_analysis\nfrom experiment.utils.isolation import IsolatedRunner\nfrom experiment.runner import ExperimentRunner\nprint('All imports successful')\n\"\n```\n\nExpected: `All imports successful`\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Verify analysis pipeline with mock data**\n\nCreate a small test script:\n\n```python\n# test_analysis.py\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom experiment.config import DEFAULT_CONFIG\nfrom experiment.metrics.analyzer import run_full_analysis\nimport tempfile\nimport json\n\n# Create mock data\ndf = pd.DataFrame({\n    \"task_id\": [f\"task_{i}\" for i in range(100)] * 2,\n    \"condition\": [\"control\"] * 100 + [\"treatment\"] * 100,\n    \"input_tokens\": [5000 + i * 100 + (0 if i < 50 else 200) for i in range(200)],\n    \"output_tokens\": [2000 + i * 50 - (300 if i >= 100 else 0) for i in range(200)],\n    \"total_tokens\": [6000 + i * 100 for i in range(200)],\n    \"success\": [True] * 85 + [False] * 15 + [True] * 87 + [False] * 13,\n    \"time_seconds\": [60 + i * 2 for i in range(200)],\n    \"iterations\": [3 + i % 5 for i in range(200)],\n})\n\nmetadata = {f\"task_{i}\": {\"difficulty\": [\"simple\", \"medium\", \"complex\"][i % 3]} for i in range(100)}\n\n# Save to temp dir\nwith tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as tmpdir:\n    csv_path = Path(tmpdir) / \"results.csv\"\n    df.to_csv(csv_path, index=False)\n    \n    results = run_full_analysis(csv_path, metadata)\n    \n    print(f\"Token mean diff: {results.token_mean_diff:.2f}\")\n    print(f\"Success rate control: {results.success_rate_control:.2%}\")\n    print(f\"Success rate treatment: {results.success_rate_treatment:.2%}\")\n    print(f\"Time median control: {results.time_median_control:.2f}\")\n    print(\"Analysis pipeline OK\")\n```\n\n```bash\npython test_analysis.py\n```\n\nExpected: `Analysis pipeline OK`\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Clean up test file and commit final state**\n\n```bash\nrm test_analysis.py\ngit status\n```\n\nExpected: No uncommitted changes (or only intentional changes)\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThis plan creates a complete expe